{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17633498","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17633498"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T17:54:04+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T17:54:04+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17482"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17482","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17482"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10172"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70730"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10172","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10172"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17482"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56196"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"5326"},{"type":"tags","id":"5359"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"23775"},{"type":"contributions","id":"23788"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70730","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/70730"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EDifferent approaches exist for addressing disparities in health outcomes across populations. These approaches vary in their underlying principles and methods for achieving better health for all.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the concept of health equity?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Treating all health conditions with equal priority","Delivering healthcare based on ability to pay","Providing identical healthcare services to all individuals","Distributing resources according to population need","Focusing solely on genetic factors affecting health"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct answer is \u003Cstrong\u003Edistributing resources according to population need\u003C/strong\u003E. Health equity involves allocating healthcare resources and interventions based on the different levels of need across populations to achieve fair outcomes. This approach recognises that different groups may require different levels of support to achieve similar health outcomes.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETreating all health conditions with equal priority\u003C/strong\u003E fails to recognise that some conditions have greater impact on population health and require proportionally more resources.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDelivering healthcare based on ability to pay\u003C/strong\u003E creates barriers to access and perpetuates health inequities by disadvantaging those with lower socioeconomic status.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EProviding identical healthcare services to all individuals\u003C/strong\u003E represents equality rather than equity, as it does not account for differing levels of need between populations.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFocusing solely on genetic factors affecting health\u003C/strong\u003E ignores the significant impact of social determinants of health such as education, housing, and environmental conditions.\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHealth equity aims to eliminate unfair and avoidable differences in health outcomes by addressing both healthcare access and the broader social determinants of health. This includes factors such as education, income, housing, and environmental conditions that influence health outcomes.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Health equity focuses on eliminating unfair and avoidable differences in health outcomes between populations.","The social determinants of health are the conditions in which people are born, grow, live, work and age that affect health outcomes.","Health equality means treating everyone the same, while health equity means providing resources according to need."],"references":["Shultz JM, Sullivan LM, Galea S. Public Health: An Introduction to the Science and Practice of Population Health. Springer Publishing Company; 2021."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56196"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17482"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56196","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/56196"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-16T13:34:43+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-16T13:35:19+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10172"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70730"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"gro